E ancient tome book bookstand~
On the page that the tome is opened to, it reads:     
     
"On the very day that the Caelumaedani had decided to leave      
the heavens to turn the tides of the Great War, the intentions      
of the Gods were self-centered and true. On the very day that      
the Caelumaedani had decided to stay in the Mortal Realm of      
Shalar, however, they had broken the bounds that nature had      
set for both themselves and the mortals.     
     
Am I the only one that sees the profundity of the wrongness      
that the other Gods are happily taking part in?      
     
Am I the only one that is disgusted by the weakness and      
insecurity that the other Gods have in their nature which      
leads them to use the mortals for their own petty games?     
     
For their offenses, they shall suffer at the hands of the very      
mortals that they regard as playthings. They will watch as the      
underestimated mortals of Shalar display their true power: That      
of independence."     
     
A barrier of magic keeps you from touching the page to turn it.     
     
~
OWNER Zethus~
#126
Before an Ornate Altar~
This chamber of dark marble is cold, drafty and smells strongly of incense.     
A bizarre statue of a goat-headed man on one knee leans over the altar, its     
snout pointing downward with its mouth slightly open, and its arms out     
forward, each serving as a torch. Dozens of lit candles surround the altar,     
and the warm, flickering light off of the dark gray, polished marble makes the     
room seem almost alive. The circular symbol makes yet another appearance here     
on the floor before the altar, where a number of offerings lie. You notice     
some writing on a plaque below the statue.     
~
